Example 3: a method that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element from the original array, starting with the first element. For instance:
every_other([1,4,7,2,5]) # => [1,7,5]

# Informal Pseudo-Code

Given an array of integers. 

Create a new array called even_integers.

Iterate through the given array one by one.
- Append the value of the elements at space 0 and even spaces to even_integers. 

After iterating through the given array, return the new array even_integers.

# Formal Pseudo-Code

START

# Given an array of integers

SET even_integers = empty array

iterator = 0

WHILE length of the array > 0
  IF iterator is 0 or even  
    Append element of the given array at space "iterator" to even_integers
    iterator = iterator + 1
  ELSE
    iterator = iterator + 1

PRINT even_integers

END
